                            <comment id="13708237" author="psteitz" created="Mon, 15 Jul 2013 04:57:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;First attempt at a patch to activate this.  Works when javadoc is explicitly invoked in maven, but not via the site goal.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13708475" author="sebb@apache.org" created="Mon, 15 Jul 2013 14:00:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;mvn javadoc:javadoc uses the BUILD section; mvn site uses the REPORTING section.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Generally if one wants to generate a report as part of site generation and stand-alone, the configuration has to appear it two places.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;See for example the apache-rat-plugin configuration in CP32.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13708514" author="psteitz" created="Mon, 15 Jul 2013 14:45:25 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks, Sebb!&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So I guess what I need to do is put in twice. I will do that and commit if there are no objections.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13711746" author="psteitz" created="Wed, 17 Jul 2013 22:43:22 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Fixed in r1504314.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13713989" author="psteitz" created="Fri, 19 Jul 2013 19:31:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Reopening to add site docs to scope.  This can be enabled by adding a &amp;lt;head&amp;gt; element to site.xml.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
